<paragraph base="F16152978" id="IAS19_165" principles="yes"><paranum>165</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 19"/><data name="paranum" value="165"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS19_P0722">An entity shall recognise a liability and expense for <xref base="F16148495" href="IAS19_0001.dita#IAS19_0001/IAS19_UN0005">termination benefits<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0366"/></ph></xref> at the earlier of the following dates:</p><ol base="F16152980" id="IAS19_L0096" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p base="F16152981" id="IAS19_P0723">when the entity can no longer withdraw the offer of those benefits; and</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p base="F16152984" id="IAS19_P0724">when the entity recognises costs for a restructuring that is within the scope of <xref base="F16228057" href="../ias37/IAS37_TOC.dita#IAS37_TOC0001" id="IAS19_X0512">IAS 37</xref>  and involves the payment of termination benefits.</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>